<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="31Jan1925"><font color="red">31 January 1925</font> <i>BLHW</i> (to Harriet Weaver): I send you the rest of Shaun &mdash; only the typescript because the French Shaun charged 12 francs for the MS. I have not found out why &mdash; revenge or a new rule. Tonight it is too late &lsquo;as I am rushing for the post&rsquo;. I shall send the MS separately. <i>Day Sorker</i> etc is De sorger for vandflod i verdens marken jeg ligger med lyst torpedo imder arker / last lines of the same poem by Ibsen is let you arrange for a new deluge over the world and I&apos;ll lay my torpedo under the ark. </div>
